"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-11-paris-2024-olympics-brume-vows-to-bounce-back-from-disappointing-outing\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria long jump star, Ese Brume has vowed to bounce back from the disappointment of her poor showing at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Brume was one of Nigeria's medal hopefuls leading to Paris 2024 but failed to live up to expectations.  The 27-year-old won bronze medal in the women's long jump three years ago.  The Commonwealth champion, however, finished in fifth position this time around.  Brume confessed he was hampered by injury.  \\\"To be honest, it was an amazing experience for me,\\\" Brume told Making of Champions.  \\\"Looking back to where I am coming from, I did not compete much this year because of injuries.  \\\"Even up to today, I also competed with an injury, but I am glad that I made it this far. I am happy with myself and thankful to God.\\\"  EPL: He will score goals - Ten Hag hails Man United star despite missing open net  Friendly: Iheanacho, Ejuke named in Sevilla's squad for Liverpool clash  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Paris 2024 Olympics: Reuben launches Nigeria's final search for medal  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"